<TITLE> Army keep their hopes alive in V-Day hockey </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 8 (bdnews24.com) - Bangladesh Army Tuesday brightened their final berths in the Dhaka Bank Victory Day Hockey Tournament with a 2-1 win over holders Bangladesh Krira Shikkha Protisthan (BKSP) at Moulana Bhasani National Hockey Stadium. Skipper Sirajul Islam put Army ahead in the 15th minute while Ferdous Goldar doubled the margin before Moniruzzaman Roky reduced the margin for BKSP in the 31st minute. With the fourth win in five outings, Army joined Sonali Bank, and they have to wait for their fate till the last match between Sonali Bank and BKSP. BKSP have six points from four outings, two points less than Sonali Bank's eight points from four games. 
